[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784626832&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784626832&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

It takes some sorting out, but it was UKC.AC.UK that refused to
forward to UNIDO.UUCP, which is in Germany.  The ultimate destination,
UKLIRB.UUCP, is also in Germany.

I suspect this was a reply to a message that had been distributed
by the news programs.  In general, each machine that handles
the message adds itself to the FROM line of the message header.
This is done for historical reasons.  When news started there
was no registry of UUCP machines so the names were relative and
it was necessary to have the whole path for the names to
be usable.  Now most of the UUCP machines are registered so it
is no longer necessary to have the whole path in the FROM line.
At best having the whole path on the from line just delays
a reply by sending it though needless machines.  In the
case of the reply it question, it caused the reply to be
rejected.

Bruce Orchard

